---
import rap from '../../assets/images/DrumMixers/rap.png';
import TwoColumnSection from '../unitComponents/TwoColumnSection.astro';
import Tred from "../../assets/images/AsphaltStorage/redT.png";
import AcordeonItem from '../unitComponents/AcordeonItem';
import binUnit1 from '../../assets/images/BinUnits/binUnit1.png';
import img1 from "../../assets/images/RapBins/RAProv3.png";
import img2 from "../../assets/images/RapBins/RAProv1.png";
import img3 from "../../assets/images/RapBins/RAProv2.png";
import RAProv5 from "../../assets/images/RapBins/RAProv5.png";
---
<section class="w-full font-bold">
    <div class="w-full h-[100px] bg-gradient-to-b from-blueMain to-grisT">

    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 bg-grisT px-8 md:px-52">
        <div class="w-full col-span-1">
            <img src={rap.src} alt="" class="w-3/4">
        </div>
        <div class="w-full col-span-2 text-white flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">RAP COLLAR</h1><br>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin">
                The drum collar is engineered to provide the controlled and efficient entry of Recycled Asphalt Pavement (RAP)
                 into the mixing zone. Fed directly from the RAP bin via a dedicated conveyor, the material enters the drum
                  smoothly and uniformly.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-52 bg-grisT text-white">
        <h1 class="text-end text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">RAP ENTRY FLIGHTS</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 bg-grisT px-8 md:px-52">
        <div class="w-full col-span-1">
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-white">
                For recycled asphalt pavement (RAP), dedicated entry flights are used, to gently introduce RAP into the hot aggregate stream.
                 Its design allows short, uniform drops that optimize heat transfer while minimizing blue smoke and preventing material buildup.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full col-span-2 text-white flex flex-col justify-center">
            
             <img src=´´ alt="" class="w-3/4">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full bg-grisT px-8 md:px-52 py-10 flex justify-center">
        <div class="w-4/5">
            <img src={img1.src} alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex flex-col justify-end items-end space-y-2">
        <div class="h-0.5 w-1/3 bg-blueMain"></div>
        <div class="h-0.5 w-1/5 bg-redBg"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-redBg py-16">
        <h1>With Triaso, Become the Exclusive Provider of Hot Mix for <br> All Paving Projects in Your Region</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-52">
        <img src={RAProv5.src} alt="" class="rounded-lg w-3/5">
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 px-8 md:px-52 items-center">
        <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">We undestand the importance to keep your equipment running non-stop</h2><br>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin">Equipped with large-capacity RAP bins, this feeding process handle high material
                 volumes while maintaining uniform distribution. The system is designed to prevent buildup, ensuring a uniform
                  flow into the drum mixer without interruption.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full">
            <img src={img2.src} alt="" class="rounded-lg w-3/4">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-52">
        <img src={img3.src} alt="" class="w-3/5">
    </div>
   <TwoColumnSection
                leftBg="bg-redBg"
                rightBg="bg-blueMain"
                imageSrc={Tred.src}
                imageAlt="Red T icon"
                imageWidth="150px"
                >
                    <div slot="left" class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-3">
                        <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">INCORPORATING RAP FEEDERS</h1>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
                            By incorporating RAP feeders, asphalt plants can improve RAP integration, enhance mix consistency,
                             and promote sustainable production by efficiently reintegrating recycled materials into the asphalt mix.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div slot="right" class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-3">
                        <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">
                           AVAILABLE IN 10 OR 25-TONS
                        </h1>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
                            With configurations of one, two, or three RAP bin units
                        </p>
                    </div>
    </TwoColumnSection>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5 gap-10 items-start justify-center">
        <div class="col-span-2 flex justify-center">
            <img src={binUnit1.src} alt="" class="w-1/2 md:w-full"/>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-3 flex flex-col items-start h-full justify-center md:pr-52 pr-8 md:pl-0 pl-8">
            <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-5xl font-bold">Precision Dosing <br>Systems in <br>RAP feeders</h1><br>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-thin text-grisT text-justify">
                Our RAP bins are equipped with precision dosing systems designed for reliable material control, ensuring proper
                 dosage according to the mix recipe, meeting tight production tolerances and plant performance standards.
            </p><br>
            <div class="w-full flex flex-col gap-6 pr-10">
                <AcordeonItem client:only title="High-Precision Sensors" content="Integrated sensors monitor material levels in real time, allowing for precise control of dosing quantities and preventing overflows or shortages.">
                </AcordeonItem>
                <AcordeonItem client:only title="Adjustable Flow Rates" content="The system allows operators to modify the flow rate, accommodating a wide range of materials, from fine aggregates to larger-sized rocks or sand.">
                </AcordeonItem>
                <AcordeonItem client:only title="Consistent Material Distribution" content="Ensures uniform dosing to maintain a balanced mixture in downstream operations, such as mixing or crushing processes.">
                </AcordeonItem>
                <AcordeonItem client:only title="Automated Controls" content="Equipped with programmable logic controllers (PLCs), the system can be automated for consistent and repeatable performance across different projects.">
                </AcordeonItem>
                <AcordeonItem client:only title="Anti-Clogging Mechanism" content="Specially designed chutes and gates minimize the risk of blockages, ensuring a smooth and uninterrupted material flow.">
                </AcordeonItem>
                <AcordeonItem client:only title="Energy-Efficient Operation" content="Engineered to optimize power usage, reducing operational costs while maintaining high performance.">
                </AcordeonItem>
            </div>
            <div class="text-lg md:text-xl font-thin text-grisT text-justify py-10">
                <p>
                    These features make our RAP bin dosing systems essential for operations that require precise and efficient
                     incorporation of RAP, meeting tight production tolerances and plant performance standards.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

</section>